latestPosts.caption:
Just a little reminder this summer to wear what you want! I’m definitely guilty of ‘I’ll just lose some weight and then I can wear x’, but if I’m honest that moment never comes because when I ‘fix’ one ‘flaw’ I then move on to the next. We’re bombarded with images of what an ideal body looks like, what the latest ‘look’ is changing from year to year but the unrealistic unattainable feel remains the same.

If you don’t fit that ideal size and do wear what you want, you’re either vilified or maybe worse at times, glorified with backhanded comments like ‘wow you’re so brave’… 

I’d love to see more normalisation of just wearing what we want. What feels good. Whatever your shape / size etc. Because honestly my body and the way a bikini or shorts fit me is the LEAST interesting thing about me. 

Thanks for coming to my TED talk 😝
